==Old English==
===Etymology===
Common Germanic *''[[breuwan]]'', whence also Old Saxon ''breowan'', ''brewan'' (Dutch ''[[brouwen]]''), Old High German ''[[briuwan]]'' (German ''[[brauen]]''), Old Norse ''[[brugga]]'' (Swedish ''[[brygga]]'', Danish ''[[brygge]]'').  Perhaps akin to Latin [[defrutum]]. The original meaning seems to have been "to prepare by heat".
===Verb===
'''brēowan'''

